# API Configuration
API_BASE=http://url-to-api/v1
API_KEY=
MODEL_NAME=

# HuggingFace Token (for higher rate limits with sentence-transformers)
HF_TOKEN=

# Embedding Model Configuration
EMBEDDING_MODEL=
EMBEDDING_API_BASE=http://url-to-embedding-api/v1
EMBEDDING_API_KEY=
SIMILARITY_THRESHOLD=0.75

# Processing Options
API_TIMEOUT=90
IMAGE_DPI=150
CONTEXT_PAGES=3

# Logging (DEBUG, INFO, WARN, ERROR). Default WARN
LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# Vision Model Prompt (for slow path analysis)
# Use {context_count} to inject the number of known pages in the prompt
VISION_PROMPT="Analyze these document pages and determine if the last page is part of the same continuous document as the preceding pages.

The first {context_count} pages are believed to be from the same document. Is the last page part of the same document?

Look for:
- Consistent headers, footers, page numbers
- Continued text flow across pages
- Similar formatting and layout
- Thematic continuity

Notes:
- Bills from doctors, hostpitals, etc., often provide flyer-type information after the main correspondance. In such cases, things like flyers/advertisements for related services, e.g. payment processing, should be considered part of the same document if the first page's page numbering implies it, e.g. the first page says \"page 3 of 4\" and the next page is is a flyer or something somehow related to the first page.

Respond with JSON:
{
  \"same_document_confidence\": integer (-100 to 100),
  \"reasoning\": \"string explaining the decision\"
}"